SIMPLE: unharness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unharness
<hw>Un*har"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>harness</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To strip of
harness; to loose from harness or gear; <as>as, to <ex>unharness</ex>
horses or oxen</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To disarm; to divest of armor.</def>
<rj><au>Holinshed.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unhasp</ent>⟦br⟧
